The paper deals with a classical problem in computer science and mathematics, which has applications in many fields, including statistics. The paper proposes improved solutions for rounding a real matrix to an integer one with minimal rounding errors. This problem is related to data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.LG), and scientific computing (cs.SI).
